        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Define the CellWithMeta data structure — represents a single table cell with text lines, merge spans, and visibility. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Table cell data: lines, colspan, rowspan, annotations, serialization. \par \b Input\/ \:  Lines list, colspan, rowspan, invisible flag. \par \b Output\/ \:  CellWithMeta instance convertible to API schema. \par \b Links\/ \:  [INHERITS(5): Serializable, USES_API(8): ApiCellWithMeta, READS_DATA_FROM(9): LineWithMeta] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>lines is never None (defaults to empty list)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>colspan &gt;= 1, rowspan &gt;= 1 \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why use colspan/rowspan rather than pre-expanded cells? A: This preserves the original table structure information, allowing the consumer to decide how to flatten/display. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 – Added semantic markup and LDD logging] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
<para>CLASS 10[Table cell with metadata] =&gt; CellWithMeta METHOD 6[Get merged text] =&gt; get_text METHOD 7[Merge annotations] =&gt; get_annotations METHOD 8[API schema conversion] =&gt; to_api_schema \par \b Use Cases\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>[CellWithMeta]: TableReader → CreateCell → CellWithMetaStoredInTable </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
